          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "What is USB-C PD 3.1?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "USB Power Delivery 3.1 (PD 3.1) is a major revision of the USB charging protocol introduced by the USB-IF in 2021. Its defining feature: it doubles the maximum power over a single USB-C cable from 100W to 240W by adding Extended Power Range (EPR) with new 28V, 36V, and 48V voltage levels. This enables charging gaming laptops, workstations, monitors, and even e-bikes through the same USB-C connector used for phones."
