          "name": "What is the difference between PD 3.0 and PD 3.1?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "PD 3.0 supports up to 100W (20V × 5A) using Standard Power Range (SPR). PD 3.1 adds Extended Power Range (EPR) with new voltage levels at 28V, 36V, and 48V, enabling up to 240W (48V × 5A). PD 3.1 also introduces AVS (Adjustable Voltage Supply) for finer voltage control between 15V-48V. PD 3.1 chargers and cables are backward compatible with PD 3.0 devices, but EPR requires both an EPR-rated charger and EPR-rated cable."
