            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "PPS (Programmable Power Supply) is a PD 3.0 feature that adjusts voltage in 20mV steps from 3.3V to 21V — ideal for smartphone fast charging (Samsung Super Fast Charging, iPhone fast charge). AVS (Adjustable Voltage Supply) is a PD 3.1 feature that adjusts voltage in 100mV steps from 15V to 48V — designed for laptops, monitors, and high-power devices. PPS handles precision at lower voltages; AVS handles range at higher voltages. Many PD 3.1 chargers support both."
