                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-brandBlue uppercase italic mb-6">1. PD 3.0 vs 3.1 vs 3.2: What OEM Buyers Must Verify Before Specifying Charger ICs</h2>
                    <div class="overflow-x-auto">
                        <table class="w-full border border-slate-200 rounded-xl">
                            <thead class="bg-brandBlue text-white">
                                <tr>
                                    <th class="text-left p-3 font-black uppercase text-xs">Feature</th>
                                    <th class="text-center p-3 font-black uppercase text-xs">PD 3.0</th>
                                    <th class="text-center p-3 font-black uppercase text-xs">PD 3.1</th>
                                    <th class="text-center p-3 font-black uppercase text-xs">PD 3.2</th>
                                </tr>
                            </thead>
                            <tbody>
                                <tr class="border-t border-slate-200"><td class="p-3 font-bold text-sm">Max Power</td><td class="p-3 text-center">100W</td><td class="p-3 text-center text-brandBlue font-bold">240W</td><td class="p-3 text-center">240W (same)</td></tr>
                                <tr class="border-t border-slate-200"><td class="p-3 font-bold text-sm">Voltage Levels</td><td class="p-3 text-center">5V, 9V, 15V, 20V</td><td class="p-3 text-center text-brandBlue font-bold">+28V, 36V, 48V</td><td class="p-3 text-center">Same as 3.1</td></tr>
                                <tr class="border-t border-slate-200"><td class="p-3 font-bold text-sm">Power Ranges</td><td class="p-3 text-center">SPR only</td><td class="p-3 text-center text-brandBlue font-bold">SPR + EPR</td><td class="p-3 text-center">Same</td></tr>
                                <tr class="border-t border-slate-200"><td class="p-3 font-bold text-sm">Adjustable Voltage</td><td class="p-3 text-center">PPS (3.3-21V, 20mV steps)</td><td class="p-3 text-center text-brandBlue font-bold">PPS + AVS (15-48V)</td><td class="p-3 text-center">AVS refined</td></tr>
                                <tr><td class="p-3 font-bold text-sm">What It Means</td><td class="p-3 text-center text-slate-600 text-sm">Phones, tablets, ultrabooks</td><td class="p-3 text-center text-slate-600 text-sm">+ Gaming laptops, workstations, monitors</td><td class="p-3 text-center text-slate-600 text-sm">Polished version of 3.1</td></tr>
                            </tbody>
                        </table>
                    </div>
                    <p class="text-slate-600 mt-4"><strong>PD 3.2 note:</strong> PD 3.2 does NOT increase power beyond 240W. It's a protocol refinement that standardizes AVS behavior, improves charger-device negotiation, and fixes edge cases discovered in early PD 3.1 implementations. Think of it as PD 3.1 "polished and production-hardened."</p>
