                            </tbody>
                        </table>
                    </div>
                    <p class="text-slate-600 mt-4"><strong>Bottom line:</strong> For most people in 2026, PD 3.0 with a 5A cable is all you need. PD 3.1 EPR only matters if you own a MacBook Pro 16" or a gaming laptop that charges above 100W via USB-C. Don't pay for 240W capability you won't use — but do buy a charger that supports PPS for optimal smartphone fast charging.</p>

